  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some side dishes for tortellini?",
  "response": "Tortellini is a versatile pasta that pairs well with a variety of side dishes. Here are some ideas:\n\n1. **Garlic Bread:** A classic choice, garlic bread complements the rich flavors of tortellini with its crispy texture and buttery, garlicky taste.\n\n2. **Mixed Green Salad:** A light salad with a vinaigrette dressing can balance the richness of tortellini. Consider adding ingredients like cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, and olives.\n\n3. **Caprese Salad:** Fresh mozzarella, tomatoes, and basil drizzled with balsamic glaze offers a refreshing and vibrant side.\n\n4. **Roasted Vegetables:** Roasting vegetables like zucchini, bell peppers, and asparagus brings out their natural sweetness and makes a hearty side.\n\n5. **Grilled Brussels Sprouts:** These bring a slightly charred and nutty flavor that pairs well with creamy or cheesy tortellini dishes.\n\n6. **Saut\u00e9ed Spinach or Kale:** Lightly saut\u00e9ed greens with garlic and olive oil add a healthy, fresh element to the meal.\n\n7. **Antipasto Platter:** Including cured meats, cheeses, olives, and marinated vegetables for a Mediterranean flair.\n\n8. **Minestrone Soup:** A bowl of this hearty vegetable soup can serve as both a starter and a complementary side.\n\n9. **Panzanella:** An Italian bread salad made with chunks of stale bread, fresh tomatoes, cucumbers, and a tangy dressing.\n\n10. **Roasted Mushrooms:** Simple and earthy, roasted mushrooms can be flavored with herbs and garlic to match the pasta.\n\nThese options can complement the flavors of the tortellini and provide a well-rounded meal.",
